diff --git a/infra/RUNBOOK_news_agent.md b/infra/RUNBOOK_news_agent.md
index 10c8fdb..0a6d0ea 100644
--- a/infra/RUNBOOK_news_agent.md
+++ b/infra/RUNBOOK_news_agent.md
@@ -28,3 +28,74 @@
 - Verify consumer groups:
   - `XINFO GROUPS stream:news_raw`
   - `XINFO GROUPS stream:news_norm`
+
+
+## Rollout plan (safe, staged)
+
+### Stage 0 — Ingest + DB only (no LLM)
+Goal: quantify volume/noise and verify dedup/normalization.
+
+1) Run `news_ingest` + `news_norm` + Postgres.
+2) Keep `news_reasoner` stopped.
+3) Monitor:
+   - `news_norm_processed_total{status="ok"}`
+   - `news_norm_quarantine_total{reason=...}`
+   - `news_stream_lag_ms{stream="stream:news_raw"}`
+
+Rollback: stop `news_norm` (ingest may continue spooling into stream:news_raw).
+
+### Stage 1 — Enable LLM events (still no impact on trade)
+Goal: verify contract events and budgets.
+
+1) Start `news_reasoner`.
+2) Verify:
+   - `XLEN stream:news_events` grows
+   - `news_llm_overbudget_total` stays near 0
+   - `news_budget_usd_used / news_budget_usd_limit` < 0.9
+3) UI feed can subscribe to `stream:news_events` (contract schema v1).
+
+Rollback: stop `news_reasoner` (ingest+norm continue).
+
+### Stage 2 — Publish priors, trade ignores (shadow)
+Goal: validate prior cadence and staleness without affecting execution.
+
+1) Keep priors publishing ON in reasoner (default).
+2) Trade core must treat news priors as shadow (ignore) or soft flags only.
+3) Monitor:
+   - `news_prior_published_total`
+   - Redis keys `news:prior:<SYMBOL>` TTL
+
+Rollback: disable prior consumption in trade core (`NEWS_PRIOR_ENABLE=0`) or
+stop only the consumer that reads priors.
+
+### Stage 3 — Enable NewsPriorGate soft/tighten
+Goal: allow *only risk tightening* (no direction changes).
+
+1) Trade core: enable gate in `soft` profile (flags only).
+2) Canary: switch small % to `tighten`.
+3) Observe execution KPIs: fill-rate, slippage, veto rate, PnL distribution.
+
+Rollback: set profile back to `soft` (or disable gate).
+
+### Stage 4 — Optional narrow hard profile
+Goal: veto only in narrow, well-defined conditions.
+
+Enable only after you have statistics on:
+- false positives for `pump_pattern` and `leaders_conflict`
+- correlation with adverse selection.
+
+Rollback: hard → tighten → soft.
+
+
+## Rollback quick switches
+
+- Stop reasoner without stopping ingest:
+  - `docker compose stop news_reasoner`
+
+- Disable trade-side usage:
+  - `NEWS_PRIOR_ENABLE=0` (trade core)
+
+- Tight budget protection:
+  - lower `NEWS_MAX_DOC_CHARS`
+  - raise `NEWS_MIN_IMPACT_PUBLISH`
+
